headline: Newmont (NEM) Is Up 9.3% After Record Free Cash Flow and Leadership Shift - What's Changed
summary: In recent months, Newmont has benefited from higher gold prices, strong Q3 2025 results with near-zero net debt, and record free cash flow, supported by new production from its Ahafo North mine in Ghana. At the same time, upcoming leadership changes and the company’s sharpened focus on core assets after several divestments could meaningfully influence how it balances growth projects, costs, and cash returns.
